NAME
       unicode_start - put the console in Unicode mode.


SYNOPSIS
       unicode_start [ font [ screen-font-map ] ]


DESCRIPTION
       The  unicode_start  command  puts  both the screen and the
       keyboard in Unicode mode, and maybe load  the  given  font
       and  screen-font  map.   If no args are given, the current
       font and screen-font map will be used.


BUGS
       You might get into trouble if you don't have a screen-font
       map loaded.


SEE ALSO
       unicode_stop(1), consolechars(8).



